label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to osmotic stress

value.value: A gene expression phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of translation in response to osmotic stress is abnormal. Translation may be down-regulated to a greater extent than normal, and may not be restored to normal levels post-stress.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to oxidative stress

value.value: A gene expression phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of translation in response to oxidative stress is abnormal. Translation may be down-regulated to a greater extent than normal, and may not be restored to normal levels post-stress.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to nitrogen starvation

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which regulation of translation in response to nitrogen starvation is abnormal. Translation may be down-regulated to a greater extent than normal, and may not be restored to normal levels upon prolonged nitrogen starvation.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: inviable cell upon G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell fails to resume growth after several days in G0 phase. The inviable cells show some features characteristic of apoptosis, including loss of DNA.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants. The population term 'loss of viability upon G0 to G1 transition' (FYPO:0006660) may also be relevant.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more MluI cell cycle box factor elements (MCBs) occurs to a greater extent than normal.
A cell population phenotype in which the size, shape, or structure of invasively growing filaments is abnormal.

label.value: normal growth on ammonia nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in a medium containing ammonia as the nitrogen source.

label.value: normal growth on proline nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cells grow normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type) in a medium containing L-proline as the nitrogen source.

label.value: loss of viability upon nutrient depletion

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells are deprived of nutrients such as carbon or nitrogen.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown under nutrient-depleted conditions, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to nutrient-replete conditions is measured and compared to wild type. Also consider 'sensitive to nitrogen starvation' (FYPO:0002124).

label.value: loss of viability in stationary phase

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after entering stationary phase.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown to stationary phase, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon return to conditions supporting vegetative growth is measured and compared to wild type.

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a cell population grows only in the presence of an antioxidant in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on ammonia nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing ammonia as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on proline nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing L-proline as the nitrogen source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on galactose carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing galactose as the carbon source.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterothallic haploid cells spontaneously form cells with diploid DNA content at a higher frequency than normal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA reductase (NADPH) activity is increased.

label.value: increased protein processing during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the observed occurrence of protein processing is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased nuclear protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in the cell nucleus is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mutations occur at a higher frequency than normal.

A phenotype that shows no detectable differences from normal. In fission yeast, the characteristics of wild type cells of the sequenced strain (972 h-) or the isogenic h+ or h90 strains are regarded as normal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which regulation of transcription during the G1/S phase of the cell cycle is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal cellular response to reactive oxygen species during G0

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cells do not respond normally to reactive oxygen species, resulting in accumulation of oxidative damage including DNA damage, during G0 phase.

label.value: abnormal regulation of translation in response to stress

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which regulation of translation in response to stress is abnormal.

An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of a microtubule-destabilizing substance than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to DNA damage.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to DNA damage in culture. If you have assayed the response to DNA damage at the subcellular or molecular level, consider annotating to 'abnormal cellular response to DNA damage stimulus' (FYPO:0000157). Also consider specific phenotype terms for sensitivity to substances or other stimuli that can damage DNA, e.g. 'sensitive to DNA damaging agents' (FYPO:0000266), 'sensitive to methyl methanesulfonate' (FYPO:0000089), 'sensitive to UV' (FYPO:0000268), etc.

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a genotoxin, any chemical compound that can act to induce direct or indirect DNA damage. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of a DNA damaging agent that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to ionizing radiation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to ionizing radiation.

label.value: sensitive to UV during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to ultraviolet light.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a microtubule-destabilizing substance. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of a microtubule-depolymerizing drug that allows wild type cells to grow.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to osmotic stress.

definition.value: Use this term if you have assayed growth of cells exposed to osmotic stress in culture. If you have assayed the response to osmotic stress at the subcellular or molecular level, consider annotating to 'abnormal cellular response to osmotic stress' (FYPO:0000193).

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a salt stress.
A septation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell fails to form a septum.
An RNA metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNAs transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region are absent.

definition.value: This term encompasses both unprocessed RNA transcribed from the centromere outer repeat region and siRNAs derived by dicer-mediated processing of the primary transcripts. Use this term only for levels of RNA transcribed from endogenous centromere outer repeat sequences. For levels of RNA transcribed from an exogenous reporter gene placed in the outer repeat region, consider 'abnormal chromatin silencing at centromere outer repeat region' (FYPO:0002346).

label.value: increased duration of mitotic M phase

value.value: A cell cycle phenotype in which the duration of M phase of the mitotic cell cycle is longer than normal.
A physical cellular phenotype in which the mitotic spindle forms with microtubules emanating from only one pole.

definition.value: Also consider annotating to 'abnormal spindle pole body separation' (FYPO:0001733) or one of its children.

label.value: decreased cell population growth following spore germination

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which cell population growth is decreased following spore germination, resulting in the formation of a smaller colony than normal in a given amount of time.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which conjugation does not occur.

label.value: small vacuoles present in increased numbers during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains more, but smaller, vacuoles than normal.
A chromosome segregation phenotype in which chromosomes are broken during mitotic chromosome segregation.

label.value: large and small daughter nuclei, with unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation

value.value: A mitosis phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell undergoes unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation, and as a result the nucleus divides unequally to produce one daughter nucleus that is larger than the other.
A cell population phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a population of cells grow poorly in medium that has a low concentration of manganese (Mn2+).
A physical cellular phenotype in which the amount, distribution, composition or morphology of a cell part is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects cytoskeleton organization. Cytoskeleton organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures.
